 way to recon the beasts that will soon be handing you your butt.  I dunno how easy it'd be to convince SOE to give us stat information, though.  Even post Vision, I'd suspect you'd probably make more headway teaching stones to cry.<br>
<br>
What might be more doable than getting them to code an entire new zone(s) might be to see about getting them to release an in-game series of lore books in the PoK area.  Ala, Elminster's Ecologies of AD&amp;D fame.  From an RP standpoint, if Myrist is the great library, where's half the knowledge you'd expect it to have?  Why don't they carry the old world and expansion lore books there, for that matter?  <br>
<br>
I kinda think a No Rent series of guidebooks, (hopefully illustrated, they can put an image of VS on a wall, why not add one to a book?), telling you something about the mob, such as where it lives, general information on what it likes and dislikes, (here's your resist info), etc, would greatly add to the roleplay aspect of the game.  If nothing else, it would be nice to know that the mobs actually interact in some way with their environment and other mobs, rather than just sitting around in zones waiting to be killed off by PCs.  If they can develop all these long and complex backstories for their quests and GM events (read: let's see how many players we can take out at once in DL, or seriously annoy later by changing Equestrielle around on a whim), then why not put some time into the less flashy aspects of storytelling?<br>
<br>
I guess it's may just be my continuing gripe about there seeming to be little roleplaying in this roleplaying game.  I'm sure sooner or later they'll have another event with Firiona Vie mucking around with perfectly good people and places.  I only hope I'm on hand to land a few nukes on that meddling kid and her stupid dogs.  Eat Ice Spear of Solist, Al'kabory-doo.<br>
<br>
Zerlatik Flaimweaver<br>
Sorcerer of Tholuxe Paells<br>
